      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Guard Skill Workshop update applies against delta drafts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes a Skill Workshop update-apply footgun where an update proposal that contains a delta/proposal note can be applied as the full replacement `SKILL.md`.\n\nFor update proposals, `applySkillProposal()` strips proposal frontmatter and writes the proposal body as the live skill content. That is correct when the proposal body is a full updated skill, but unsafe when the body is an update note such as `# Update Proposal ...` with \"proposed changes\" instructions. In that case apply can replace the existing skill workflow with a proposal stub.\n\nThis PR adds an apply-time guard for update proposals before the live write, while still allowing intentional complete rewrites of a skill body.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nSkill Workshop `action=update` proposals are meant to carry a complete replacement `SKILL.md`. Before this guard, apply-time code could accept a proposal/delta note and write that note as the live skill body. That risks destroying the actual skill procedure.\n\nThe guard should reject obvious non-skill update notes and identity swaps, but it should not block valid complete rewrites just because the new skill reorganizes or consolidates sections. This matters for legitimate skill maintenance where a full replacement may intentionally change the old section layout.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Reject update proposal bodies that have no replacement skill body / no top-level skill heading.\n- Reject update proposal bodies that look like delta/proposal notes instead of complete skill bodies, using multiple proposal-note markers instead of a single broad substring match.\n- Reject update proposal bodies that change the existing skill identity heading.\n- Allow complete replacement `SKILL.md` bodies that intentionally reorganize or consolidate old `##` sections.\n- Preserve compatibility for existing valid skills that have frontmatter plus prose but no top-level H1 heading.\n- Add regression coverage for:\n  - delta/proposal-note update drafts;\n  - empty replacement bodies;\n  - complete section rewrites;\n  - single proposal-like section headings inside an otherwise complete skill;\n  - emoji-decorated preserved headings.\n\n## Duplicate/adjacent work check\n\nI checked current `origin/main` and searched open/closed issues and PRs before opening this PR.\n\nNot duplicates:\n\n- #92733 touches `applySkillProposal()` for openclaw-managed skill roots, but it still writes `stripProposalFrontmatterForSkill(content)` directly and does not validate that update content is a complete skill body.\n- #94315 / #94249 cover large-proposal apply timeout behavior.\n- #90421 / #90388 cover stale proposal reconciliation when a target skill already exists or disappears.\n- #95395 / #94947 cover `action=create` proposals that should have targeted existing skills.\n\nThis PR is specifically about update-apply content-shape validation before overwriting an existing `SKILL.md`.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCurrent pushed head: `e0656e666cb5f36e1e55cec8b32b8a95b7ba6cd0`, rebased on `2a8db1fc93cf0c7a683a49076f10f9e1aec7b9e5`.\n\nExact validation run after the latest fix:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/skills/workshop/service.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nObserved results on the exact pushed head:\n\n```text\nsrc/skills/workshop/service.test.ts: 30 passed\ntsgo core-test: passed\ngit diff --check: passed\n```\n\nReal apply-time proof outside the unit test shard:\n\n```text\nA temporary isolated workspace used the actual Skill Workshop service apply path.\n\nbad delta-note update -> rejected\noriginal SKILL.md body preserved -> true\nvalid H1-less complete update -> applied\nupdated H1-less body present -> true\ninjected H1 heading -> false\ntemporary workspace -> removed\n```\n\nRedacted terminal output from that proof:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"delta-note-apply\",\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"<temp-workspace-root>/workspace\",\n  \"rejected\": true,\n  \"rejection\": \"Skill update proposal content appears to be a delta/proposal note, not a complete replacement SKILL.md. Revise the proposal with the full updated skill body before applying.\",\n  \"originalBodyPreserved\": true,\n  \"proposalStillPending\": true\n}\n{\n  \"event\": \"h1-less-complete-update\",\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"<temp-workspace-root>/workspace\",\n  \"applied\": true,\n  \"updatedBodyPresent\": true,\n  \"hasInjectedH1\": false\n}\n{\n  \"event\": \"cleanup\",\n  \"removed\": \"<temp-workspace-root>\"\n}\n```\n\nAdditional behavior covered by the focused test shard:\n\n```text\nempty replacement body -> rejected with the existing SKILL.md preserved\ncomplete section rewrite -> applied and replaced the old section structure\nsingle proposal-like section heading in a complete skill -> allowed\nemoji-decorated preserved H1 -> applied as the same skill identity\nexisting valid H1-less skill -> complete update applied without injecting H1\n```\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Full repository CI is expected to run on GitHub for the pushed head.\n",
